OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778702756
OL,3,CUS lawyer found guilty of wife and
OL,4,Cson's murders has conviction overturned
OL,6,FHe will remain in prison, where he is
OL,7,Fcurrently serving a 40-year sentence
OL,8,Fafter pleading guilty to the separate
OL,9,Fcharge of stealing around $12 million
OL,10,Ffrom his clients.
OL,12,FThe case became a true crime
OL,13,Fsensation, prompting streaming
OL,14,Fminiseries, bestselling books and
OL,15,Fdozens of podcasts.
OL,17,FMurdaugh has always denied killing his
OL,18,Fwife, Maggie, 52, and his younger son,
OL,19,FPaul, whose bodies he found outside
OL,20,Ftheir home in 2021.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
